<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Installation: The FreeBSD as a Host </font></span></div><div># The VirtualBox will be installed inside the Host Machine.</div><div># Don’t confuse this with the FreeBSD running as Guest inside other Host.</div><div> </div><div>Version: VirtualBox-5.6.2</div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt;<span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> sudo</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> portsnap fetch update</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> cd</span> <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/ports/emulators/virtualbox-ose</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> BATCH=1</span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">sudo</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> make -DBATCH install clean</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># After the installation:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># You need to load the vboxdrv kernel module via /boot/loader.conf:</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">vboxdrv_load</span>="<span style="color: rgb(0, 143, 0);">YES</span>"</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># You also have to add all users to your vboxusers group in order to use vbox.</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> sudo</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">pw groupmod</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">vboxusers</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> -m</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">khasanov</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># For bridged networking please add the following line to your /etc/rc.conf:</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">vboxnet_enable</span>="<span style="color: rgb(0, 143, 0);">YES</span>"</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># For USB support your user needs to be in the operator group and needs read</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># and write permissions to the USB device.</span></div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">sudo</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> pw groupmod</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">operator</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">-m</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">khasanov</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># Add the following to /etc/devfs.rules (create if it doesn't exist):</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">[system=10]</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">add path 'usb/*' mode 0660 group operator</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># To load these new rule add the following to /etc/rc.conf:</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">devfs_system_ruleset</span>="<span style="color: rgb(79, 143, 0);">system</span>"</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># Then restart devfs to load the new rules:</span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">sudo</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">/etc/rc.d/devfs</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);"> restart</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;">Installing the VirtualBox Additions:</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;">( FreeBSD as a Guest inside the VirtualBox Host)</span></span></div><div><br /></div><div># Note: You need this only if you have a Host machine and</div><div># you want to install the FreeBSD as a Gest.</div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> cd</span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> /usr/ports/emulators/virtualbox-ose-additions</span></div><div>=&gt; <font color="#ff2f92">sudo </font><b>make install clean </b></div><div># <font color="#ff2f92">Do NOT enable</font> the OpenGL support </div><div># If the old version found, remove first.</div><div><br /></div><div># After the installation, add the lines to your “/etc/rc.conf”</div><div><b>vboxguest_enable</b>="<font color="#009051">YES</font>"</div><div><b>vboxservice_enable</b>=“<font color="#009051">YES</font>"</div><div># If its not done yet:</div><div>=&gt;<font color="#ff2f92"> sudo</font><b> pw groupmod</b> wheel -m khasanov</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">Note: The FreeBSD does NOT support the Extension Pack!</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div></en-note>